# pgai-agent-kanban: crontab-small.example
#
# Hardware assumption: 1 core / <=8 GB RAM, or shared/low-resource host.
#
# Tier: small
# Design choice: three separate tier files (small/medium/large) rather than a
#   parameterized template.  Each file is self-contained and flows through the
#   existing __KANBAN_ROOT__ / __CLAUDE_PATH__ substitution and
#   safe_overwrite_crontab mechanism in install-crontab.sh unchanged.
#   Install with: team/scripts/install-crontab.sh  (after pointing it at this
#   file, or by substituting manually as shown below).
#
# Cadence: every 5 minutes per agent, with per-phase integer-minute offsets.
#   - Even minutes (*/5):        PM fires first.
#   - 1 minute later (1-59/5):   CM fires.
#   - 2 minutes later (2-59/5):  TESTER fires.
#   - 3 minutes later (3-59/5):  CODER fires.
#   - 4 minutes later (4-59/5):  WRITER fires.
# No --sleep sub-minute stagger is used; the full-minute offsets are sufficient
# on a single-core or shared host where parallel wake processes would contend.
#
# Maximum agent-to-agent handoff latency: ~5 minutes.
# Recommended for: single-core VMs, shared CI runners, low-budget hosts.
#
# IMPORTANT: Replace __KANBAN_ROOT__ and __CLAUDE_PATH__ with real values
# before installing.  install-crontab.sh performs these substitutions
# automatically.
#
# Manual install:
#   sed -e "s|__KANBAN_ROOT__|/your/kanban/root|g" \
#       -e "s|__CLAUDE_PATH__|/usr/local/bin|g" \
#     team/templates/install/crontab-small.example | crontab -

# --- Environment ---
PGAI_AGENT_KANBAN_ROOT_PATH=__KANBAN_ROOT__
PATH=__CLAUDE_PATH__:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

# =============================================================================
# SMALL-TIER PATTERN — every-5-minutes with integer-minute phase offsets
# =============================================================================
# Maximum wait between agent firings: 5 minutes
# No sub-minute stagger; one phase per minute to avoid resource contention.

# --- Release-phase agents: PM, CM, TESTER ---
# PM fires at :00 past every 5 minutes
*/5 * * * * __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/wake-batch.sh --agent=pm     --sleep=0  >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-pm.log 2>&1

# CM fires at :01 past every 5 minutes (1-minute offset)
1-59/5 * * * * __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/wake-batch.sh --agent=cm     --sleep=0  >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-cm.log 2>&1

# TESTER fires at :02 past every 5 minutes (2-minute offset)
2-59/5 * * * * __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/wake-batch.sh --agent=tester --sleep=0  >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-tester.log 2>&1

# --- Work-producer agents: CODER, WRITER ---
# CODER fires at :03 past every 5 minutes (3-minute offset)
3-59/5 * * * * __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/wake-batch.sh --agent=coder  --sleep=0  >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-coder.log 2>&1

# WRITER fires at :04 past every 5 minutes (4-minute offset)
4-59/5 * * * * __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/wake-batch.sh --agent=writer --sleep=0  >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-writer.log 2>&1

# --- Cleanup Script (weekly, Sundays at 4:00 AM) ---
0 4 * * 0 __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/cleanup/cleanup.sh >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-cleanup.log 2>&1

# --- Trivial-log purge (daily at 04:15, opt-in) ---
# Uncomment to enable daily purge of small stale batch logs:
# 15 4 * * * __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/cleanup/cleanup.sh --trivial-only >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-cleanup-trivial.log 2>&1

# --- OVERWATCH Tier-1 sweep (hourly at :30) ---
# Fires once per hour at minute 30 — distinct from the 5-minute agent slots
# (which land at :00, :01, :02, :03, :04 of each 5-minute cycle).
# Operator tuning: change the minute (30) to any value not in the agent
# wake slots (0, 1, 2, 3, 4 mod 5).  Use minute 30 unless CODER's
# agent timing is remapped to include it.
# Cadence is operator-adjustable: change */1 to */2 for every-2-hours, etc.
30 * * * * __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/overwatch-sweep.sh >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-overwatch-sweep.log 2>&1

# --- OVERWATCH Tier-2 deep-clean (daily at 03:30) ---
# LLM-driven review of the action log and any sweep-flagged anomalies.
# The daily cadence keeps model cost bounded; the 03:30 slot avoids the
# hourly sweep at :30 by an hour and sits during a low-traffic window.
30 3 * * * __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/wake-batch.sh --agent=overwatch --sleep=0 --max-tasks=1 >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-overwatch.log 2>&1

# --- Log Cleanup (daily at 04:30) ---
30 4 * * * __KANBAN_ROOT__/scripts/cleanup/cleanup_logs.sh >> __KANBAN_ROOT__/logs/cron-cleanup-logs.log 2>&1
